03/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- The governor's office in the southeast province of Siirt announced Tuesday (August 3rd) that three Kurdish rebels and one police officer were killed in a clash with militants from the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
The rebels attacked a police station and a housing complex in the town of Eruh using automatic weapons and rocket-propelled grenades.
One police officer was killed and another was wounded.
(AP, AFP, Voice of America, Hurriyet - 03/08/10)
